narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I gained a solid background in CFT and the current areas of interest in particle theory

This course is an introduction to conformal field theory, and an exposition to the frontiers in related areas of modern research, all of which I learned a great deal about. As an undergrad, this course also taught me about the method and tricks associated with renormalization, feynman path-integrals, and the vonformal/Virasoro algebras.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The problem sets were rather vague, and although they did do well to illustrate the material, I think it would have been helpful to have more guidance (such as hints) for the problems when they were given.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: For any aspiring theoretical physicist with at least a decent background in quantum field theory, this course is a great opportunity. Take it!
